```turtle
:ThisPaper :proposes :INBEDDER ;
    :contextText "we propose INBEDDER that instantiates this embed-via-answering idea by only fine-tuning language models on abstractive question answering tasks." .

:INBEDDER :addresses :InstructionFollowingTextEmbeddings ;
    :contextText "We address a novel and challenging problem: instruction following of text embeddings and propose a framework, INBEDDER , to handle it by learning to answer user questions given inputs." .

:INBEDDER :basedOn :embed_via_answering ;
    :contextText "We offer a novel viewpoint, which treats the instruction as a question about the input text and encodes the expected answers ." .

:INBEDDER :finetunedOn :AbstractiveQA_11_200k ;
    :contextText "INBEDDER fine-tunes the LM on a union of 11abstractive question answering (QA) datasets with ∼200,000 paragraph-question-answer triplets" .

:AbstractiveQA_11_200k :relatedTo :AbstractiveQA ;
    :contextText "a union of 11abstractive question answering (QA) datasets with ∼200,000 paragraph-question-answer triplets" .

:INBEDDER :uses :StopwordRemoval ;
    :contextText "We further simplify the answers by removing all the stopwords" .

:INBEDDER :achievesScore "2.89" ;
    :contextText "resulting in an average answer length of2.89tokens." .

